farmer			Being a Farmer
farmer_1			In Leek Wars you play a Farmer.
As soon as you register you get a level 1 leek. Your goal is to defeat other leeks thanks to the coding and improvement of your AI using LeekScript.
farmer_2			Your leeks will earn Experience points after each fight. These Experience points will determine the level of your leeks. The higher your level, the better the chips and weapons you can use. When your level increases you can spend new capital points to upgrade your leek.
farmer_3			Later on in the game, you will have the opportunity to raise up to 4 leeks if you comply with the following:
farmer_4			1st leek: available as soon as registered.
farmer_5			2nd leek: 10,000 Habs / 1st leek at level 50.
farmer_6			3rd leek: 100,000 Habs / 1st leek at level 100 / 2nd leek at level 50.
farmer_7			4th leek: 1,000,000 Habs / 1st leek at level 150 / 2nd leek at level 100 / 3rd leek at level 50.
farmer_8			Reaching higher levels for your leek will allow you to use more LeekScript functions.
Each function is rated with a level which is displayed on the right of the function name in the <a href='/help/documentation'>documentation</a>. These level is the mimimum requested to be allowed to use this specific LeekScript function.
fights			Fights
fights_1			All information related to fights are available on the Garden page. There are 4 different kinds of fights:
fights_2			Solo fight (1 vs 1): one of your leeks is fighting another leek.
fights_3			Farmer fight: all your leeks fight all the leeks of another farmer.
fights_4			Team fight: one composition of your team is fighting another composition of another team.
fights_5			Royal battles : one of your leeks is fighting 9 other leeks.
fights_6			Your daily fights not been done on day can be postponed to the day after. If you cannot perform the fights (due to any other IRL constraint) you will have the opportunity to trigger them the day after. The postponing is done only the day after. If you do not perform your late fights the day after, they are definitively lost. For example, if you have no time today to do the <b>50</b> daily fights, you will then have the possibility to perform <b>100</b> fights tomorrow.
fights_7			The allowed number of fights is reset every day at midnight. (New fights for the new day, plus potentially the postponed fights from yesterday).
fights_8			Solo Fights
fights_9			In a <b>solo fight</b> your leek is against another leek which has mainly the same power (automatically calculated by the game).
fights_10			A fight will be counted, and removed to your remaining daily fights.
fights_11			Farmer Fights
fights_12			All your leeks fight all the leeks of another farmer.
fights_13			Although all your leeks fight, it counts only for a fight.
fights_14			Team Fights
fights_15			All the leeks inside a composition of your team fight together all the leeks of a composition of another team. Each of your leek is allowed to do <b>10</b> team fights with its composition, apart from your daily fights. A composition is allowed to fight only if all its leeks have at least 1 team fight left.
fights_16			Team fights do not add up to the total of your wins, draws and losses (ratio).
fights_17			Royal battles
fights_18			One of your leeks is fighting 9 other leeks. You can do as much royal battles as you want, but they begin only when 10 leeks are registered. Royal battles 
				are available at the level 50.	
				
fights_19			Royal battles reward no Experience point nor Habs. Royal battles do not add up to the total of your wins, draws and losses (ratio).
habs			Habs
habs_1			Hab(s) is the name of the Leek Wars currency. You earn Habs thanks to fights. You spend Habs to buy weapons and chips in the market, or to recruit an additional leek.
